{
  "_comment": "Change-scoped gating manifest (plan 021 §2.5). Maps each live gate script to the source globs it exercises, so `npm run gates:changed` can run only the gates whose coverage intersects a diff. Globs deliberately err toward OVER-inclusion: over-covering just runs an extra gate; under-covering ships a real break unguarded. `determinismCritical` paths bypass scoping entirely and escalate to the FULL board (region/rng/clip/tileCache feed every generator — a change there can break any gate's determinism). Glob syntax: `**` = any path segments, `*` = any non-slash chars.",
